snippet.textDisplay: Take it or leave it, the word behind the lines in the UFC managerial office had been leaked to suggest that Conor was promised a knockout win over Cerone in order to try to solidify his brand name once again and to make him a valid contender. A loss would have devastated PPV sales, the revenue base, and endorsements. This was a brainstorm idea that was set in place by UFC brass in order to keep their "cash-cow" viable. Conor brings in an entire country of sales with him from all over the world that could be estimated to gross millions of dollars. The UFC will be very careful about how they match Conor up in the future with other opponents for this very reason only. The UFC is a business and it needs the influx of cash on a regular basis in order to stay afloat. As Conor falls from notariety so will the revenue base of the UFC fall with him. Interrogate Cerone and get the real truth.
